caption.text: When good plans turn bad... Never knew that I am supposed to retell the origin story of the heart to understand the etiology of congenital heart diseases :"D

Uhh OK the last caption sounds like I am a privileged wuss

This is Enneacampus ansorgii, also known as the African freshwater pipefish. The guy is one of several species of freshwater pipefish (they're usually more saltwater) that can be kept properly in saltwater (others eventually need more brackish water), and trying to feed things (mine is fed frozen waterfleas, btw) has been quite a challenge, but look at how cute it is!

The story of how this African weirdo (and another individual) got to be in my possession involves buying, of course, but that's not the point

The more proper point to make here is that fishkeeping has been an awesome part of my life (aside from others). To be able to keep (and hopefully breed, later on) fishes from various corners of the globe, and be supported financially and morally whilst doing so, is a rare and precious gift indeed

Thanks mom & dad, thanks lil sister

And also a honourable mention for one of the stores in the Sumenep, Jakarta ornamental fish market, across the bait shop (you should go there to understand the vast diversity of fishes, and who knows, you might also fell in love)
